data.name: WriteToClosedPipeline
data.value: The WriteObject and WriteError methods cannot be called after the pipeline has been closed. Please contact Microsoft Support Services.

data.name: WriteNotPermitted
data.value: The WriteObject and WriteError methods cannot be called from outside the overrides of the BeginProcessing, ProcessRecord, and EndProcessing methods, and only from that same thread. Validate that the cmdlet makes these calls correctly, or please contact Microsoft Support Services.

data.name: PipelineNotStarted
data.value: Cannot complete pipeline operation because it hasn't been started yet. You must call the Begin() method before calling End() on a steppable pipeline.

data.name: FirstCommandCannotHaveInput
data.value: Cannot run the pipeline because the first cmdlet in the pipeline is trying to read input from a previous cmdlet. Either modify the first cmdlet, remove the first cmdlet, or add the cmdlet whose output is needed by the first cmdlet, then execute the pipeline again.

data.name: PipelineExecuteRequiresAtLeastOneCommand
data.value: Cannot run pipeline because there are no commands. Add at least one command to the pipeline and run it again.

data.name: InvalidRemoteCommand
data.value: Runspace object has a null remote command associated with it. A disconnected RemotePipeline object cannot be created because there is no remote command to connect to.

data.name: ActionPreferenceStop
data.value: Cannot continue to run cmdlet because all cmdlet execution was stopped by the Stop policy. Determine why cmdlet run was stopped.

data.name: InvalidCommandNumber
data.value: Cannot process the cmdlet number. The ReadFromCommand function must specify the Id of a cmdlet that has already been added to the pipeline. Please contact Microsoft Support Services.

data.name: ConnectNotSupported
data.value: This pipeline does not support disconnect-connect semantics.

data.name: PipeAlreadyTaken
data.value: Cannot read the output specified by the ReadFromCommand and ReadErrorQueue functions because another cmdlet is already reading that output. Please contact Microsoft Support Services.

data.name: CannotCreatePipeline
data.value: An error occurred creating the pipeline

data.name: ExecutionAlreadyStarted
data.value: Cannot perform the operation because the pipeline is started. Stop the pipeline and try the operation again.

data.name: PipelineNotDisconnected
data.value: Cannot connect this pipeline because it is not in the disconnected state.

data.name: SecondFailure
data.value: A cmdlet threw an exception after calling ThrowTerminatingError. The first exception was "{0}" with stack trace "{1}". The second exception was "{2}" with stack trace "{3}". Determine why these exceptions were thrown and try again.

data.name: CommandProcessorAlreadyUsed
data.value: Cannot process the cmdlet instance because the cmdlet instances is being used by another pipeline. Please contact Microsoft Support Services.
